### replace 0 instead of Np.nan in our cementatious material
Data['Calcined Clay(Kg/m3)'] = Data['Calcined Clay(Kg/m3)'].replace(np.NaN , 0)
Data['Cement(Kg/m3)'] = Data['Cement(Kg/m3)'].replace(np.NaN , 0)
Data['Silica Fume(Kg/m3)'] = Data['Silica Fume(Kg/m3)'].replace(np.NaN , 0)
Data['Calcined Kaolin(Kg/m3)'] = Data['Calcined Kaolin(Kg/m3)'].replace(np.NaN , 0)
Data['Fly Ash(Kg/m3)'] = Data['Fly Ash(Kg/m3)'].replace(np.NaN , 0)
Data['Blast Furnace Slag(Kg/m3)'] = Data['Blast Furnace Slag(Kg/m3)'].replace(np.NaN , 0)
In [25]:
### Compute W/B in our data
Binder = Data['Calcined Clay(Kg/m3)'] + Data['Cement(Kg/m3)'] + Data['Silica Fume(Kg/m3)'] + Data['Calcined Kaolin(Kg/m3)'] + Data['Fly Ash(Kg/m3)'] + Data['Blast Furnace Slag(Kg/m3)']
Data['W/B'] = Data['Water(Kg/m3)']/Binder
